  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7079.62 sitting below the GEX flip at 7098, dealers are currently in stabilizing mode and likely buying this dip as they're long gamma in the PIN regime. The massive +7010M gamma wall at 7200 creates significant resistance where dealers will aggressively sell any rally, while the thick positive gamma between 7100-7150 should provide strong support and dampen volatility. Key levels to watch: break above 7098 flip puts dealers in selling mode toward 7100-7125 resistance, while any push toward 7040 (-947M negative gamma) would trigger aggressive dealer buying.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect bouncy, range-bound action between 7040-7125 with upside capped near 7100.",
